I can’t click elements in your browser from here. I can, however, give you code/snippets you can run where the page is running. Pick the one that fits your environment.

1) In the browser console (quick):
document.querySelector('#submit-button')?.click();

2) Browser console with check:
const btn = document.querySelector('#submit-button');
if (btn) btn.click();
else console.warn('No element found with selector #submit-button');

3) Wait until present then click (plain JS):
function waitFor(selector, timeout = 5000) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    const start = Date.now();
    const timer = setInterval(() => {
      const el = document.querySelector(selector);
      if (el) { clearInterval(timer); resolve(el); }
      else if (Date.now() - start > timeout) { clearInterval(timer); reject('timeout'); }
    }, 100);
  });
}
waitFor('#submit-button', 10000).then(el => el.click()).catch(e => console.warn(e));

4) Puppeteer (Node):
await page.waitForSelector('#submit-button', { visible: true });
await page.click('#submit-button');

5) Playwright (Node/Python):
await page.click('#submit-button'); // Playwright waits by default

6) Selenium (Python):
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.support.ui import WebDriverWait
from selenium.webdriver.support import expected_conditions as EC
btn = WebDriverWait(driver, 10).until(EC.element_to_be_clickable((By.CSS_SELECTOR, '#submit-button')))
btn.click()

If the button is hidden or disabled, you may need to make it visible/enable it or dispatch mouse events:
const btn = document.querySelector('#submit-button');
btn.removeAttribute('disabled');
btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));

